Feature: User Authentication # specs/features/authentication.feature:1
  As a registered user
  I want to authenticate securely
  So that I can access the system according to my role
  Feature: User Authentication  # specs/features/authentication.feature:1

  Scenario: User logs in successfully               # specs/features/authentication.feature:14
    Given the Supabase authentication is configured # specs/steps/system_steps.py:37
    And the following users exist:                  # specs/steps/system_steps.py:42
      | email               | role    | full_name    |
      | admin@empresa.com   | admin   | Admin User   |
      | analyst@empresa.com | analyst | Analyst User |
      | viewer@empresa.com  | viewer  | Viewer User  |
    Given I am on the login page                    # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:7
    When I enter valid credentials                  # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:95
    Then I am redirected to the dashboard           # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:189
    And my role is displayed in the header          # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:195

  Scenario: User logs in with invalid credentials           # specs/features/authentication.feature:20
    Given the Supabase authentication is configured         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:37
    And the following users exist:                          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:42
      | email               | role    | full_name    |
      | admin@empresa.com   | admin   | Admin User   |
      | analyst@empresa.com | analyst | Analyst User |
      | viewer@empresa.com  | viewer  | Viewer User  |
    Given I am on the login page                            # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:7
    When I enter invalid credentials                        # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:104
    Then I see an error message "Invalid email or password" # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:199
    And I remain on the login page                          # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:205

  Scenario: User session expires                              # specs/features/authentication.feature:26
    Given the Supabase authentication is configured           # specs/steps/system_steps.py:37
    And the following users exist:                            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:42
      | email               | role    | full_name    |
      | admin@empresa.com   | admin   | Admin User   |
      | analyst@empresa.com | analyst | Analyst User |
      | viewer@empresa.com  | viewer  | Viewer User  |
    Given I am logged in                                      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    When my session expires after inactivity                  # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:137
    Then I am redirected to the login page                    # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:209
    And I see a message "Session expired, please login again" # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:213

  Scenario: User profile loads after login          # specs/features/authentication.feature:32
    Given the Supabase authentication is configured # specs/steps/system_steps.py:37
    And the following users exist:                  # specs/steps/system_steps.py:42
      | email               | role    | full_name    |
      | admin@empresa.com   | admin   | Admin User   |
      | analyst@empresa.com | analyst | Analyst User |
      | viewer@empresa.com  | viewer  | Viewer User  |
    Given I am logged in as "analyst@empresa.com"   # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
    When I navigate to my profile                   # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:143
    Then I see my full name, email, and role        # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:217
    And I can update my profile information         # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:221

Feature: Companies Management # specs/features/companies.feature:1
  As an analyst or admin
  I want to manage company registry data
  So that monthly cost records can be associated with companies
  Feature: Companies Management  # specs/features/companies.feature:1

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Register a new company           # specs/features/companies.feature:11
    Given the API is running                 # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given I am on the "New Company" page     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:11
    When I fill in the company form:         # specs/steps/company_steps.py:81
      | field        | value              |
      | company_id   | EMP001             |
      | empresa      | Empresa Alpha      |
      | cnpj         | 98.765.432/0001-10 |
      | razao_social | Alpha Ltda         |
      | cliente      | João Silva         |
      | email_envio  | joao@alpha.com     |
    And I save the company                   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:100
    Then the company is created successfully # specs/steps/company_steps.py:257
    And the API returns status 201           # specs/steps/company_steps.py:262
    And I see the company in the list        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:267

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Company requires mandatory fields           # specs/features/companies.feature:27
    Given the API is running                            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                  # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given I am on the "New Company" page                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:11
    When I leave "empresa" empty                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:86
    And I save the company                              # specs/steps/company_steps.py:100
    Then I see a validation error "Empresa is required" # specs/steps/company_steps.py:276
    And the company is not created                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:287

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Company CNPJ must be unique                                 # specs/features/companies.feature:35
    Given the API is running                                            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                                  # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a company exists with CNPJ "12.345.678/0001-90"               # specs/steps/company_steps.py:59
    When I try to create another company with CNPJ "12.345.678/0001-90" # specs/steps/company_steps.py:91
    And I save the company                                              # specs/steps/company_steps.py:100
    Then I see a validation error "CNPJ already exists"                 # specs/steps/company_steps.py:276
    And the company is not created                                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:287

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View companies list                                # specs/features/companies.feature:43
    Given the API is running                                   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given companies exist in the system                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:19
    When I navigate to "Companies" page                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:250
    Then I see a list of all active companies                  # specs/steps/company_steps.py:292
    And each company shows: company_id, empresa, cnpj, cliente # specs/steps/company_steps.py:296

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View company details                                            # specs/features/companies.feature:50
    Given the API is running                                                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                                      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP001"                         # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    When I click on the company                                             # specs/steps/company_steps.py:224
    Then I see the full company details                                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:303
    And I see all fields: empresa, cnpj, razao_social, cliente, email_envio # specs/steps/company_steps.py:308

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Update company information              # specs/features/companies.feature:57
    Given the API is running                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                              # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP001" # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    And I am on the company detail page             # specs/steps/company_steps.py:15
    When I click "Edit Company"                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:141
    And I change the cliente to "Maria Santos"      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:145
    And I click "Update"                            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:149
    Then the company is updated                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:314
    And the cliente shows "Maria Santos"            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:319

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Deactivate a company                          # specs/features/companies.feature:67
    Given the API is running                              # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                    # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP001"       # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    When I click "Deactivate Company"                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:172
    And I confirm company deactivation                    # specs/steps/company_steps.py:176
    Then the company is marked as inactive                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:325
    And it no longer appears in the active companies list # specs/steps/company_steps.py:331
    But its monthly records are preserved                 # specs/steps/company_steps.py:342

  @admin
  Scenario: Delete a company                          # specs/features/companies.feature:76
    Given the API is running                          # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP003"   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    When I click "Delete Company"                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:198
    And I confirm company deletion                    # specs/steps/company_steps.py:202
    Then the company is permanently removed           # specs/steps/company_steps.py:348
    And all its monthly records are deleted (CASCADE) # specs/steps/system_steps.py:412

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot create companies         # specs/features/companies.feature:84
    Given the API is running                       # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                             # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given I am logged in as "viewer"               # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
    When I navigate to the companies page          # specs/steps/company_steps.py:243
    Then I do not see a "New Company" button       # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:60
    And I cannot access the creation page directly # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:229

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot edit companies       # specs/features/companies.feature:91
    Given the API is running                   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a company exists                     # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:25
    And I am logged in as "viewer"             # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
    When I view the company details            # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:42
    Then I do not see an "Edit" button         # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:233
    And I cannot access the edit page directly # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:237

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot delete companies  # specs/features/companies.feature:99
    Given the API is running                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a company exists                  # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:25
    And I am logged in as "viewer"          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
    When I view the company details         # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:42
    Then I do not see a "Delete" button     # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:64

Feature: Cost Centers Management # specs/features/cost_centers.feature:1
  As an analyst or admin
  I want to manage cost centers
  So that operational costs can be categorized
  Feature: Cost Centers Management  # specs/features/cost_centers.feature:1

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Create cost center                   # specs/features/cost_centers.feature:10
    Given I am logged in                         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given I am on the "New Cost Center" page     # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:72
    When I fill in the cost center form:         # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:84
      | code        | INF                      |
      | name        | Infrastructure           |
      | description | Server and hosting costs |
    And I click "Save"                           # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:88
    Then the cost center is created successfully # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:147
    And I see the cost center in the list        # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:152
    And the cost center is active                # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:158

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View cost centers list                      # specs/features/cost_centers.feature:22
    Given I am logged in                                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given cost centers exist in the system              # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:18
    When I navigate to "Cost Centers" page              # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:80
    Then I see a list of all active cost centers        # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:163
    And each cost center shows: code, name, description # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:167

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Update cost center                          # specs/features/cost_centers.feature:29
    Given I am logged in                                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a cost center exists with code "INF"          # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:68
    And I am on the cost center detail page             # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:76
    When I click "Edit"                                 # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:118
    And I change the name to "Infrastructure & Hosting" # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:122
    And I click "Save"                                  # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:88
    Then the cost center is updated                     # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:171
    And the name shows "Infrastructure & Hosting"       # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:176

  @admin
  Scenario: Deactivate cost center              # specs/features/cost_centers.feature:39
    Given I am logged in                        # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a cost center exists with code "INF"  # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:68
    When I click "Deactivate"                   # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:126
    And I confirm the deactivation              # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:130
    Then the cost center is marked as inactive  # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:180
    And it no longer appears in the active list # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:185

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot create cost centers      # specs/features/cost_centers.feature:47
    Given I am logged in                           # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given I am logged in as "viewer"               # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
    When I navigate to the cost centers page       # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:14
    Then I do not see a "New Cost Center" button   # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:225
    And I cannot access the creation page directly # specs/steps/auth_steps.py:229

Feature: Monthly Cost Records # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:1
  As an analyst
  I want to enter monthly cost data per product
  So that the controller team can track expenses month by month
  Feature: Monthly Cost Records  # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:1

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Add monthly record for a product        # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:11
    Given the API is running                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                              # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given company "EMP001" exists                   # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:36
    When I add a monthly record:                    # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:237
      | field          | value      |
      | mes_ano        | 2026-01-01 |
      | elegiveis      | 100        |
      | vidas_cobradas | 95         |
      | valor_final    | 15000.00   |
    And I save the monthly record                   # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:284
    Then the monthly record is created successfully # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:458
    And the monthly API returns status 201          # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:464

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Duplicate month detection                                            # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:24
    Given the API is running                                                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                                           # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given company "EMP-DUP" exists                                               # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:36
    And a monthly record for "EMP-DUP" + "2026-01-01"                            # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:67
    When I try to add another record for the same company + month                # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:271
    And I save the monthly record                                                # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:284
    Then I see a monthly validation error "Record already exists for this month" # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:476

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Add multiple records for same company   # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:32
    Given the API is running                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                              # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given company "EMP001" exists                   # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:36
    When I add a monthly record:                    # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:237
      | field       | value      |
      | mes_ano     | 2026-02-01 |
      | valor_final | 15000.00   |
    And I save the monthly record                   # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:284
    Then the monthly record is created successfully # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:458

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View monthly records for a company           # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:42
    Given the API is running                             # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                   # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given company "EMP001" has monthly records           # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:175
    When I retrieve monthly records for company "EMP001" # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:351
    Then I see all monthly records for that company      # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:494
    And each record shows: mes_ano, valor_final          # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:500

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View records filtered by month                        # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:49
    Given the API is running                                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given monthly records exist for "2026-01-01" and "2026-02-01" # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:191
    When I filter records by month "2026-01-01"                   # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:374
    Then I see only records from January 2026                     # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:508
    And I do not see February records                             # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:515

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View all records across companies          # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:56
    Given the API is running                           # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                 # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given monthly records exist for multiple companies # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:218
    When I retrieve all monthly records                # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:386
    Then I see records from all companies              # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:521
    And I can filter by company_id                     # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:527

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Update a monthly record                           # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:63
    Given the API is running                                  # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                        # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a monthly record exists for "EMP001" + "2026-01-01" # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:108
    When I update the record:                                 # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:323
      | field       | value    |
      | valor_final | 16000.00 |
    And I save the update                                     # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:82
    Then the monthly record is updated                        # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:470
    And the valor_final shows 16000.00                        # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:486

  @admin
  Scenario: Delete a monthly record                           # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:73
    Given the API is running                                  # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                        # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a monthly record exists for "EMP001" + "2026-01-01" # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:108
    When I delete the monthly record                          # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:333
    Then the record is permanently removed                    # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:532
    And I get 404 when retrieving it                          # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:538

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot create monthly records  # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:80
    Given the API is running                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given I am logged in as "viewer"              # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
    When I try to create a monthly record         # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:396
    Then the monthly operation is denied          # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:546

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot edit monthly records  # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:86
    Given the API is running                    # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a monthly record exists               # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:8
    And I am logged in as "viewer"              # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
    When I try to update the monthly record     # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:419
    Then the monthly operation is denied        # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:546

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot delete monthly records  # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:93
    Given the API is running                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:52
    Given a monthly record exists                 # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:8
    And I am logged in as "viewer"                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:59
