Feature: Data Model # specs/system/data_model.feature:1
  As a database administrator
  I want a well-defined data model
  So that data integrity is maintained
  Scenario: Core tables exist          # specs/system/data_model.feature:6
    Given the database is initialized  # specs/steps/system_steps.py:86
    Then table "profiles" exists       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:313
    And table "companies" exists       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:313
    And table "monthly_records" exists # specs/steps/system_steps.py:313
    And table "audit_logs" exists      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:313

  Scenario: Company data has proper constraints  # specs/system/data_model.feature:13
    Given a company is created                   # specs/steps/system_steps.py:113
    Then the cnpj field is unique                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:318
    And the company_id field is unique           # specs/steps/system_steps.py:331
    And the is_active flag defaults to true      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:343

  Scenario: Monthly records have unique constraint                   # specs/system/data_model.feature:19
    Given a monthly record is created                                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:117
    Then the combination of company_id + produto + mes_ano is unique # specs/steps/system_steps.py:356
    And each record is linked to a valid company                     # specs/steps/system_steps.py:368
    And financial fields use DECIMAL type                            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:381

  Scenario: Financial data uses proper types  # specs/system/data_model.feature:25
    Given a monthly record is created         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:117
    Then valor_final uses DECIMAL type        # specs/steps/system_steps.py:142
    And valor_elegivel uses DECIMAL type      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:154
    And rs_carregado uses DECIMAL type        # specs/steps/system_steps.py:166
    And amounts cannot be negative            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:398

  Scenario: Referential integrity is enforced          # specs/system/data_model.feature:32
    Given a company is referenced by monthly records   # specs/steps/system_steps.py:121
    When the company is deleted                        # specs/steps/system_steps.py:125
    Then all its monthly records are deleted (CASCADE) # specs/steps/system_steps.py:412
    And no orphaned records exist                      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:129

Feature: Security Model # specs/system/security_model.feature:1
  As a system architect
  I want robust security policies
  So that data is protected at all levels
  Scenario: RLS policies enforce role hierarchy           # specs/system/security_model.feature:6
    Given the role hierarchy is: admin > analyst > viewer # specs/steps/system_steps.py:78
    When a "viewer" attempts to create a cost             # specs/steps/system_steps.py:200
    Then the operation is denied                          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:285
    When an "analyst" attempts to delete a cost           # specs/steps/system_steps.py:207
    Then the operation is denied                          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:285
    When an "admin" performs any operation                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:213
    Then the operation is allowed                         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:289

  Scenario: Authentication is required for all operations  # specs/system/security_model.feature:15
    Given an unauthenticated user                          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:70
    When they attempt to access any protected resource     # specs/steps/system_steps.py:218
    Then they receive a 401 Unauthorized response          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:293

  Scenario: Audit trail captures all changes          # specs/system/security_model.feature:20
    Given a cost is created, updated, or deleted      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:182
    Then an audit log entry is created                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:297
    And the log contains the old and new values       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:303
    And the log contains the user who made the change # specs/steps/system_steps.py:308

Feature: System Overview # specs/system/system_overview.feature:1
  As a controller team
  I want a monthly cost tracking system
  So that I can manage company benefits costs (Gympass, Wiipo, Flex) month by month
  Scenario: System provides company management  # specs/system/system_overview.feature:6
    Given the system is deployed                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:28
    Then users can register companies           # specs/steps/system_steps.py:224
    And users can view company details          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:229
    And users can deactivate companies          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:234

  Scenario: System provides monthly cost tracking         # specs/system/system_overview.feature:12
    Given the system is deployed                          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:28
    Then users can enter monthly cost records per product # specs/steps/system_steps.py:239
    And users can view costs month by month               # specs/steps/system_steps.py:244
    And users can filter by company and month             # specs/steps/system_steps.py:249
    And each month shows all products for that company    # specs/steps/system_steps.py:254

  Scenario: System enforces role-based access control       # specs/system/system_overview.feature:19
    Given a user is authenticated                           # specs/steps/system_steps.py:65
    When the user has role "viewer"                         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:188
    Then they can only view data                            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:192
    When the user has role "analyst"                        # specs/steps/system_steps.py:188
    Then they can create and update data                    # specs/steps/system_steps.py:196
    When the user has role "admin"                          # specs/steps/system_steps.py:188
    Then they can perform all operations including deletion # specs/steps/system_steps.py:273

  Scenario: System maintains data security via RLS          # specs/system/system_overview.feature:28
    Given the database has Row Level Security enabled       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:74
    Then users can only access data according to their role # specs/steps/system_steps.py:277
    And all data access is enforced at database level       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:281

